Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
read_sai(25.10)                                                read_sai(25.10)

Name
       read_sai

Syntax
       read_sai

       [-help]

       [<name>]

       [-partial]

       [-reduce_by_flexfiller]

       [-rule_only]

       Enables the SoC Architecture Information (SAI) mode that allows the use
       of SAI commands interactively at the command line.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <name> Specifies the SAI file name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -partial
              When  specified,  it enables SAI to support designs loaded using
              the restoreDesign command. Use this  option  to  enable  partial
              netlist support in the SAI mode.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -reduce_by_flexfiller
              When  specified,  it  adds  flexfillers  in  hinsts added by the
              add_module and create_module commands. Use this option to reduce
              the size of the generated SAI netlist using the FlexFiller tech-
              nology that is same as the FlexModel methodology. This helps  to
              address the capability and run-time limitations of a growing de-
              sign size (10 or 100 of million instances).

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -rule_only
              When specified, the rules are imported only in the SAI file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The  following command reads in the example2.0.sai file and reduces the
       SAI netlist while maintaining the module areas:

       read_sai example2.0.sai -reduce_by_flexfiller

